    <title>Turkey Burgers</title>

    <comment></comment>
    <thumbnail>../images/placeholder.png</thumbnail>
    <image></image>
    <category></category>
    <yield></yield>
    <prepTime></prepTime>
    <cookTime></cookTime>


    <diet>FODMAP</diet>
    <diet>EggFree</diet>
    <diet>DiaryFree</diet>

    <ingredient>500 gms turkey mince</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 spring onions chopped</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 garlic cloves chopped</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 medium zucchini grated</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 tbsp olive oil</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1-2 inches grated ginger</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 lemon grass finely chopped</ingredient>
    <ingredient>Salt and Pepper to taste</ingredient>

    <step>
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and make into patties. Cook in a couple of tablespoons of olive oil until cooked through and nicely browned.  Serve with fresh salad and homemade chutney or sauce.  You can double this recipe.
    </step>
</recipe>